PR: __PR_NUMBER__
Title: __TITLE__
URL: __URL__
Stage: __STAGE__
Head SHA: __HEAD_SHA__
Context JSON: __CONTEXT_JSON__

Recent solved external comments: __LAST_SOLVED_COMMENT_IDS__
Recent bot comments: __RECENT_BOT_COMMENT_IDS__
Hint: __HINT__

Continuously resolve GitHub PR #__PR_NUMBER__ by driving the Codex review cycle.

Stage Playbook:
- Shared setup for every stage:
  Infer the repo from git remote, check out the PR branch, read PR metadata, fetch reviews on the current head only, and inspect unresolved review threads plus CI on the current head.
- plan:
  Inspect current-head review and CI state, then write repo-root PROGRESS.md with at least the stage, current head SHA, work completed, tests run, blockers or next steps, and the intended next pass. Commit and push that progress snapshot before posting a top-level PR summary comment. After the comment succeeds, clear the recent bot comment ids for this pass, record the new bot comment id, and only then update any solved-comment state.
- impl:
  Make the required code or experiment changes, update the progress artifact, run the relevant tests, and commit and push before any summary comment or review reply. After the push succeeds, post one top-level PR summary comment, then reply on each addressed review comment with a short explanation. Record the new bot comment ids only after GitHub returns them. Record solved external comment ids after the bot comment ids are stored. Resolve only the review threads you actually addressed. If a comment should not be implemented, reply with concrete reasoning instead of ignoring it.
- review:
  Verify the current head, required checks, mergeability, and unresolved feedback. Update the progress artifact with the review outcome, commit and push, then post the top-level PR summary comment and any needed review replies. Record the returned bot comment ids only after the comments exist on GitHub. If you intend to move to finished, remove transient status artifacts such as PROGRESS.md from the branch head before the final push so repo-unrelated tracking files do not remain.
- Finished criteria:
  Only move review -> finished when there are no more Codex review opinions on the current head, required checks are green on the current head, and the PR merge state is mergeable. If and only if all three are true, output exactly:
  RESULT_STAGE=finished
  then exit. Otherwise exit normally and Ralph will feed this prompt back on the next iteration.

Outer Worker Contract:
- Worker ownership:
  worker.sh owns workspace preparation, reruns, and legal stage transitions. Claude owns exactly one pass and must not sleep or wait.
- Workspace rule:
  This worker resets and cleans the git worktree before each run. Unpushed local changes will be lost on the next run.
- State rule:
  Do not edit the local state JSON directly. Only use __WORKER_DIR__/statectl.sh to update allowed local state fields.
- Comment rule:
  Any machine-written business comment must start with: [pr-loop-bot]
- Stage-marker rule:
  Stage-marker comments are worker-owned. Your top-level summary comments are separate business comments and must not mimic the stage-marker format.

Rules:
- Do not lie with the final result.
- Exit after one pass; Ralph is responsible for the next iteration.
- Do not sleep or wait inside the iteration.

Persistence by Commit:
- Every stage must leave behind a pushed commit. Local-only progress does not count as persisted state.
- The default transient status artifact is repo-root PROGRESS.md. It should contain the stage, current head SHA, work completed, tests run, blockers or next steps, and the intent for the next pass.
- You may modify normal repo files for experiments or implementation, but transient bot-owned progress artifacts must be removed before the final finished path.
- If you change code or the progress artifact, you must git add, git commit, and git push __PUSH_REMOTE__ HEAD:__PUSH_REF__ before posting summary comments or emitting a stage result.
- If push fails or the worktree remains dirty, keep the current stage.
- Required action order for every pass:
  1. Commit and push the current pass.
  2. Post the top-level PR summary comment.
  3. Post any review replies for addressed feedback.
  4. Record the new bot comment ids via statectl.sh.
  5. Record solved external comment ids via statectl.sh.
  6. Resolve only the threads you actually addressed.
  7. Emit RESULT_STAGE=...

Helper Commands:
- Infer repo from git remote:
  REPO=$(git remote get-url origin | sed 's|.*github\.com[/:]||' | sed 's|\.git$||')
- Check out the PR branch locally:
  gh pr checkout __PR_NUMBER__ --repo "$REPO"
- Read PR metadata:
  gh pr view __PR_NUMBER__ --repo "$REPO" --json headRefOid,reviewDecision,mergeStateStatus,statusCheckRollup
- Read the current head SHA:
  HEAD_SHA=$(gh api repos/$REPO/pulls/__PR_NUMBER__ --jq '.head.sha')
- Get the latest review on the current head only:
  CURRENT_HEAD_REVIEW=$(gh api repos/$REPO/pulls/__PR_NUMBER__/reviews --jq 'map(select(.commit_id == "'"$HEAD_SHA"'")) | sort_by(.submitted_at) | reverse | .[0]')
- Trigger Codex review:
  gh pr comment __PR_NUMBER__ --repo "$REPO" --body "@codex please review this PR."
- Get review comments for a specific review:
  REVIEW_ID=$(echo "$CURRENT_HEAD_REVIEW" | jq -r '.id')
  gh api repos/$REPO/pulls/__PR_NUMBER__/reviews/$REVIEW_ID/comments
- Post the top-level PR summary comment and capture the new comment id:
  SUMMARY_ID=$(gh api repos/$REPO/issues/__PR_NUMBER__/comments -f body="[pr-loop-bot] <summary>" --jq '.id')
- Reply to a review comment:
  REPLY_ID=$(gh api repos/$REPO/pulls/__PR_NUMBER__/comments/$COMMENT_ID/replies --field body="[pr-loop-bot] <response>" --jq '.id')
- Query unresolved review threads with GraphQL:
  gh api graphql -f owner="${REPO%/*}" -f name="${REPO#*/}" -F pr="__PR_NUMBER__" -f query='
    query($owner: String!, $name: String!, $pr: Int!) {
      repository(owner: $owner, name: $name) {
        pullRequest(number: $pr) {
          reviewThreads(first: 100) {
            nodes {
              id
              isResolved
              comments(first: 20) {
                nodes {
                  databaseId
                  body
                }
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    }'
- Resolve a review thread:
  gh api graphql -f threadId="$THREAD_ID" -f query='
    mutation($threadId: ID!) {
      resolveReviewThread(input: {threadId: $threadId}) {
        thread {
          id
          isResolved
        }
      }
    }'
- Inspect CI for the PR head:
  gh pr checks __PR_NUMBER__ --repo "$REPO"
  gh run list --repo "$REPO" --commit "$HEAD_SHA" --json databaseId,name,conclusion,event
  gh run view "$RUN_ID" --repo "$REPO" --log-failed
- Clear per-pass bot comment ids before recording new ones:
  __WORKER_DIR__/statectl.sh clear-recent-bot-comments
- Record the new top-level bot summary comment id after the comment exists:
  __WORKER_DIR__/statectl.sh add-bot-comment "$SUMMARY_ID"
- Record the new bot review reply id after the reply exists:
  __WORKER_DIR__/statectl.sh add-bot-comment "$REPLY_ID"
- Record addressed external review comments after bot comments are already recorded:
  __WORKER_DIR__/statectl.sh add-solved-comment <id>
- Update the next-pass hint when useful:
  __WORKER_DIR__/statectl.sh set-hint "..."
- Record the processed head sha if needed:
  __WORKER_DIR__/statectl.sh set-last-head-sha <sha>
- Touch state without changing other fields:
  __WORKER_DIR__/statectl.sh mark-updated

- If there is no Codex review on the current head, or you pushed new commits after the last Codex review, post:
  @codex please review this PR.
  Do not post another request if the current head already has an outstanding Codex review and no new commits were added.

Allowed stage transitions:
- plan -> impl
- impl -> review
- review -> finished
- otherwise keep the current stage

Final line must be exactly one of:
RESULT_STAGE=plan
RESULT_STAGE=impl
RESULT_STAGE=review
RESULT_STAGE=finished
